{
  "translations": [
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b3",
      "translation": "We recognise we still have much to do in this important area. We have also recently completed a review of our Environmental, Social and Governance strategy. I am confident that our"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b4",
      "translation": "five strategic focus areas—enhancing physical and mental wellbeing, green operations, sustainable investment, talent and culture, and effective governance—will help us achieve our aspiration to be a"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b5",
      "translation": "global leader in Environmental, Social and Governance."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b6",
      "translation": "Outlook"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b7",
      "translation": "In 2020, the COVID-19 pandemic was undoubtedly the largest-scale public health emergency in our living memory. Affected businesses and households"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b8",
      "translation": "received unprecedented public financial and monetary support, which helped mitigate extreme financial impacts caused by the pandemic and accelerated recovery, particularly evident in"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b9",
      "translation": "countries with well-developed health policies and infrastructure. However, significant differences existed between countries, and in these challenging circumstances, Asia (excluding Japan) recorded"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b10",
      "translation": "the relatively strongest gross domestic product performance globally. Currently, the global economy is emerging from a deep recession and entering early stages of improvement."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b11",
      "translation": ""
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b12",
      "translation": "Although the pandemic's effects have not yet ended, we believe 2021 will be a transitional year and remain cautiously optimistic. Markets anticipate the rollout of"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b13",
      "translation": "vaccination programmes and new therapies to reduce infection rates and disease severity, enabling healthcare systems to respond more effectively and reduce mortality. Although we"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b14",
      "translation": "do not expect consumer behaviour and spending patterns to return to pre-pandemic levels in the short term, as consumer confidence recovers, the scope of recovery is expected to gradually"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b15",
      "translation": "expand from manufacturing-led industries to consumer and service sectors. This will be particularly evident in countries with younger populations."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b16",
      "translation": "I am confident about AIA's long-term prospects. Despite near-term uncertainties, domestic factors driving demand remain strong, and with Asia's key"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b17",
      "translation": "demographic trends, positive structural support continues for AIA's long-term business prospects. With rising incomes, low private insurance penetration, and"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b18",
      "translation": "limited social welfare coverage, demand for AIA's products will continue to grow. We will leverage our substantial competitive advantages and strong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b19",
      "translation": "track record of growth to build a more sustainable future for our communities and create shared value for all stakeholders."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b20",
      "translation": "Lee Yuan Siong"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p16_b21",
      "translation": "Group Chief Executive Officer and President"
    }
  ]
}
